Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">The proposed introduction of a residence test for civil legal aid claimants, so as to limit legal aid to those with a “strong connection” with the UK – ‘the </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">residence test</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">’</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">The proposed </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">restriction on the scope of legal aid available to prisoners – ‘prison law’</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">The proposal that providers of legal services in applications for judicial review against public bodies should only be paid for work done on the case if the Court grants permission</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> for the application to proceed – ‘judicial review’</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> and</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">d)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">The proposal that legal aid should be removed fo</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">r all cases assessed as having </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">borderline</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> prospects of success – ‘borderline cases’</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">The Ministry of Justice has estimated that t</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">he four proposed cha</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">nges </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">could save</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">£</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">8</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">million</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> (excluding implementation costs).</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> In doing so, </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">the Government is endan