 of access to the courts, central to the UK common law, would be impeded and the principles of non-discrimination and equ</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">ality would be infringed. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">There are four elements to the proposed </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">residenc</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">e test</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">, each of which could create significant issues for individuals who may require legal aid to access justice:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">‘Lawful’</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> – determining</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> whether</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> a person is lawfully resident </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">may </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">in itself </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">require access to the courts. Legal aid, however, would not be available to </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">re</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">solve a dispute as to the lawfulness of residence.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">‘Residence’</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> – </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">British children resident abroad</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> could be precluded</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> from obtaining legal aid to bring a claim in th</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">e Family Court that they should be returned to the UK. It would also preclude persons wrongly removed from the UK</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">from being eligible for legal aid to pursue their claim</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> for damages and/or lawful return</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">‘Continuously’</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> – </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">a person who r</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">esided in the UK for </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">six months and then</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> left the UK for periods amounting to more than 30 days could not rely on the previous period of six months to accumulate the qualifying 12 month period</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">d)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">‘12 month period’</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> – </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">a British citizen </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">or E</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">uropean </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">E</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">conomic </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">rea (EEA)</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> national </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">who</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> has lived abroad for a substantial period may </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">be unable to</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> establish 12</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">months residence in the UK as holders of British </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">and EEA </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">passports </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">do</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> not have their passports stamped on entry to the UK</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">The dearth of information available about the number of cas</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">es potentially affected also means that the Government cannot project any savings that may result from the proposal, despite the fact that the ongoing annual cost of implementing the proposal (in addition to one-off set-up costs) </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">to the Legal Aid Agency</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> (L</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">AA)</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> alone </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">has been estimated at up to £1 million.</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Implications for h</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">uman </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">r</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">ights</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline"> </span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">Paragraph 3.44 of </span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Transforming Legal Aid</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> suggest</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> that the availability of legal aid may encourage people to bring disputes in England and Wales. However, the only proper connection with the UK that should be a threshold for qualification for legal aid is a jurisdictional one</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">, as</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt"> t</span><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:11pt">he protection of the la</span><span styl